Exercise 1: Using perl
Programming Exercise 1: Working with Regular Expressions
Write a program using PERL that takes in as input a text document. The program
should be able to:
a. Tokenize the texts in the document
b. Count the number of tokens and types
c. Keep track of the number and types of punctuations used
d. Search words based on user input. The user can use the wildcards * which
represents one or more character and ? which represents a single character. For
example a user search of ba* will display bag, bath, bathing, bask etc or ?at will
display cat, fat, rat etc. or combinations of the wildcards such as ?at* to display
cat, bat, bath, bathe, rat, rate, rates, etc.
